## Section 7.D — Cross-References to Other AAA Rule Sets

The Construction Rules are cross-referenced extensively with:

- The **Commercial Arbitration Rules** (default fallback for procedural questions not addressed in the Construction Rules);
- The **Optional Appellate Arbitration Rules** (for parties who have contracted for an internal appeal);
- The **Procedures for Mediation in Construction Disputes** (which may be invoked in parallel or sequentially with arbitration);
- The **Supplementary Rules for Class Arbitrations** (rarely applicable in construction matters but possible in certain multi-party owner-developer contexts).

